The paper deals with the problem of providing explanations for complex AI systems, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on the interaction between users and AI systems, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HCI). The use of symbolic planning models to provide explanations is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with sequential decision-making problems, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
